results.text: Linda was a welcoming and gracious host - making sure I was comfortable and had everything I needed. Even beyond my own stay, she also ensured that my daughters had a good time at her home with individual beds. We all enjoyed Linda's great kitchen, too, where we prepared  and enjoyed holiday meals. Linda was very responsive in communicating ahead of my stay and made sure I could reach her at any time just in case I had any questions. Linda's screened-in back porch was cozy and the large yard and decks were also very nice. The neighborhood is only a 10-minute drive from downtown and there is convenient shopping, including Whole Foods, and many restaurants nearby. This was a very nice stay!
results.title: Austin House for special events

results.text:
This is one of the first times we've been hesitant to write a review because we've been afraid of letting the secret out. :) We come to Austin fairly regularly, and we hope that this place is available for our next stay too! 
The room is quite large and luxurious. The desk and large chair came in handy for my work and my wife's studying. I don't think the pictures do it justice. The view from the expansive windows is great. You feel like you're in the trees. The windows are _very_ good sound insulators, so we slept soundly each night. The bathroom is large and beautiful, and the shower is great. 
Downstairs, we had use of the extensive, well stocked kitchen and dining room. It's worth mentioning that their coffee machine makes some of the best coffee I've ever had. 
The house is extremely well located in one of the best neighborhoods in Austin. I don't think we ever needed more than 10 minutes to get just about anywhere we needed to go, whether it was downtown, north, or south. 
Sasha and David are kind, friendly, and understanding people. We felt right at home from the moment we came in. They love cats, which was great for us, as we do too. The cats will come keep you company if you want, but are happy to leave you to your own devices if you'd prefer. So, there's no need to be a cat person to stay here - they're just an optional bonus. :) 

We wouldn't hesitate to stay here again!
results.title: ENTIRE FLOOR! Business travel & fun

results.text: Graham and I used this spot as our home base as we explored Austin to potentially move there. It is centrally located, right off Lamar, near some great restaurants, UT, and downtown. The space was quiet, clean and so pretty! Our hosts were friendly and answered our questions without being intrusive or nosy. It was really appreciated as we were weighing so many decisions, timetables and such. It was a great experience for us.

results.text: Let me start by saying that this was my first experience with airbnb and it was AWESOME!  Alexandria (and her husband) were outstanding host and the the room was outstanding as well. Its the little details in life that really make a difference and my stay could not have been more pleasing. A particular bonus was the near immediate response I received back when reserving the space and their willingness to accommodate me on such short notice (only a couple hours). Would definitely recommend to others who are looking for something up-scale  and will return back next time in Austin.

results.text:
Alexandra & husband David made my first stay at their lovely Austin so easy, comfortable, and pleasant.  Communication and responsiveness was a breeze, without ever being intrusive.  The space is so generous, well-appointed & relaxing -- guests will find themselves gazing out the bank of eastern-facing windows to soak in the striking view.  Black-out curtains will conversely handily keep any morning sun from waking guests unnecessarily early.

The neighborhood is beautiful and handily located for easy access to UT-North Campus shopping/dining, brief drive for on/off access via Loop 1 (MoPAC), as well as Lamar and/or Guadalupe.  15 minute trips to:  downtown, Ben White (71) & Capital of Texas highways (Barton Creek area), as well as Loop 1 (MoPAC) / 183 interchange.

Be aware that one must be comfortable with steps/stairs:  down to front door from street level;  up stairwell to upper level suite.  Nothing too taxing, however!

So pleased with this property and hosts, am planning to RSVP for monthly board meetings in Austin!

Alexandra and her husband were so kind. Their home is fantastic! The floor we stayed on was private, clean and very relaxing. It was difficult to leave the room at times with the large open windows looking out to a gorgeous view. It was so peaceful, we wanted to stay in all weekend!

We were in town for Valentine's Day and a race. Alexandra set out chocolates and flowers for us. Very sweet!

Thank you for having us in your lovely home. All the best from us both!

results.text: We had a great stay in Alexandra's home. The room is lovely and spacious with hotel-style amenities. There were nice fluffy towels for us to use, waters and snacks in the fridge, and a great view through the large windows. The bed was also super comfortable. It's slightly out of the way from downtown, but we took an Uber there for less than $10 each way, and the neighborhood is very beautiful. We didn't interact much with Alexandra since she was out of town, but she was very responsive and nice.

Alexandra and David were great hosts, available if we needed anything, but otherwise left us to our privacy. The room and bath were very private and really spacious and beautiful. There was a large walk-in closet that also had a refrigerator with drinks and snacks, 
and a coffeemaker. I am somewhat familiar with Austin so knew the fabulous neighborhood was convenient to downtown. I was really very happy with the location, and the 2nd floor view out over the trees of the neighboring park. I would return here in a heartbeat.
